section.section:
The parties to an agreement under this subsection and the federal government shall consider the total impact and benefits of the development of the federal enclave property on the State and on local jurisdictions, including but not limited to:
the impact on local and regional transportation;
future economic development;
the financial resources of the local jurisdiction;
the environment;
natural resource allocation;
infrastructure capacity;
employment;
disadvantaged business enterprises, minority business enterprises, and small business enterprises;
the availability and use of public services;
in-kind contributions related to the development, including the services, facilities, personal and real property, traffic mitigation, rights-of-way, and other assets and benefits of the federal government or the private developer made available to and used by the public; and
any other matter impacted by the development of the federal enclave property.

The Maryland Department of Transportation may adopt regulations to implement this section, in consultation with:
the Department;
the Department of Business and Economic Development;
the Department of the Environment;
the Department of Housing and Community Development; and
the Department of Planning.
